Commercial Analyst - SQL

What you’ll have to do:


Prepare various scenarios and propose new strategies together with the Senior Manager from the Commercial department;
Act as a business partner and adviser for the commercial department;
Prepare ad-hoc reports and draw conclusions related to profitability, actual vs. budget, product availability, active promotions, inventory levels, etc. based on requests from the commercial management team;
Variance analysis vs budget, rolling estimate and previous year;
Offer support on preparation, monitoring and review of large promotional campaigns;
Monthly analysis of the profitability and costs indicators;
Offer support on data gathering, consolidation and verifications within the commercial team;
Actively participate to commercial activities and meetings;
Discuss with the technical teams to improve some procedures and to find new solutions for effective processes;
Prepare financial calculations to support commercial initiatives (forecasting of orders, sales, inventory);
Participate in commercial activities improvement initiatives (identification, review of systems design specifications and workflows).


What makes you a good fit:


With 1-4 years of experience in a similar position (commercial & retail controlling, professional services/management consulting);
Computer literate with excellent Excel skills, SQL and database querying hands-on experience and a solid understanding of statistics and business intelligence tools;
With principles knowledge related to profitability, pricing, purchasing, commercial conditions, inventory management, promotional campaigns;
With strong interpersonal skills and effective communication (both verbal and written);
With the ability to plan and prioritize workloads to meet deadlines;
Confident, ambitious, a self-starter, team player with the ability to operate in a dynamic environment;
Fluent in English.


What we’ve prepared for you:


